Pan Seared Pork Chops with Parsnip Apple Puree

Puree:
5 tbsp butter
1 yellow onion, thinly sliced
1 lb (5 medium) parsnips, peeled and roughly chopped
2 honeycrsip apples, peeled, cored, and roughly chopped
4 garlic cloves, thinly sliced
2 tsp orange zest
1 tsp thyme leaves
1 tsp minced sage leaves
2 c chicken stock
kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste

In a 4 quart saucepna, melt the butter over medium high heat. Add the onions and cook until soft and caramelized, 12 min. Add the parsnips, apples, and garlic, and cook until golden brown, 8 min. Stir in the orange zest, thyme, and sage, and cook until fragrant, 1 min. Pour in the chicken stock and bring to a simmer. Cook until the vegetables are tender and the liquid has reduced slightly, 20 min. Working in batches, transfer to a blender and puree until smooth. Scrape back into the pan and season with salt and pepper. Keep warm until ready to serve.

Pork Chops:
2 tbsp olive oil
1 sage sprig + 12 leaves
2x12oz bone-in pork chops (1" thick)
kosher salt and freshly ground pepper to taste
5 tbsp unsalted butter
4 thyme sprigs
2 garlic cloves

In a 12" skillet, heat the olive oil over medium high heat. Line a plate with paper towels and set aside. Add the 12 sage leaves to the pan and fry until golden crisp, 10-20 sec, then transfer to the pepared plate. Season the pork chops on both sides with salt and pepper. Sear the chops, flipping once, until golden brown, 4-5 min per side. Reduce the heat to medium and add the remaining sage sprig, butter, thyme,, and garlic. Cook until the herbs are fragrant, 1 min, then return the pork chops to the pan. Cook, flipping once and basting constantly until and internal temp of 140F is reached, 3 min per side. Transfer the pork to a cutting board and let rest for 5 min before carving into thick slices.

Garnish with the fried sage leaves.
